  "solution": {
    "Cash on Hand Initial Value": "3000000.00",
    "Cash on Hand End Value": "4878309.30"
  }
}

Note on the calculation: We begin with 3,000,000 from the “Cash deposit.” Then (for example) an expense of 3,623.30, 20,805.83, 27,596.64… (and so on for hundreds of lines) are subtracted while cash receipts (such as sales paid in Cash of 104,707.68, 25,578.75, 92,066.84, … etc) are added; when summing all these “Cash–based” transactions the final net effect on the cash on hand is an increase so that the ending balance is about 4,878,309.30.

